6quot%3Ball%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20The%20good%20store%20is%20clean%20%E2%80%94%20the%20floors%20are%20swept%2C%20aisles%20open%2C%20merchandise%20in%20its%20place.%20At%20the%20bad%20one%2C%20merchandise%20is%20scattered%20all%20over%20the%20place%2C%20and%20unpacked%20boxes%20fill%20the%20aisles.%20There's%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20clear%2C%20wide%20pathway%20from%20the%20break%20room%20to%20an%20exit%20in%20case%20of%20an%20emergency%2C%20like%20a%20fire%20or%20a%20shooting.%20Instead%2C%20employees%20at%20the%20bad%20store%20have%20to%20turn%20sideways%20and%20try%20to%20shuffle%20through%20an%208-inch-wide%20gap%20between%20boxes%20piled%20high%20in%20the%20hallways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20factors%20that%20account%20for%20the%20difference%20sound%20quite%20small.%20The%20good%20store%20has%20dedicated%20recovery%20staff%2C%20whose%20job%20it%20is%20to%20put%20stuff%20where%20it%20goes.%20The%20bad%20one%20doesn't.%20The%20good%20store's%20manager%20is%20better%20at%20pushing%20for%20more%20work%20hours%20for%20employees%2C%20which%20means%20there%20are%20more%20people%20and%20time%20for%20stocking%20and%20tidying%20up%20on%20top%20of%20cashiering.%20The%20manager%20at%20the%20bad%20store%20just%20kind%20of%20lets%20anything%20fly.%20Still%2C%20Robyn%2C%20which%20is%20a%20pseudonym%2C%20says%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20blame%20is%20on%20corporate.%20She%20was%20an%20assistant%20manager%20in%20the%20past%2C%20and%20she's%20heard%20what%20goes%20on%20in%20the%20weekly%20calls.%20Rather%20than%20try%20to%20revive%20struggling%20stores%2C%20she%20said%2C%20they're%20left%20out%20to%20dry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20look%20at%20their%20trend%20of%20sales%2C%20and%20if%20a%20store%20is%20underperforming%2C%20then%20instead%20of%20maybe%20investing%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20hours%20there%20to%20try%20to%20pick%20it%20back%20up%2C%20they're%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20well%2C%20it's%20not%20worth%20investing%20in%20this%20store'%20because%20it%20is%20not%20making%20us%20whatever%20amount%20of%20money%20they%20think%20it%20should%20be%20making.%20It%20makes%20the%20problem%20worse%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Dollar%20Tree%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20have%20probably%20had%20experience%20shopping%20in%20their%20own%20version%20of%20Robyn's%20%26quot%3Bbad%26quot%3B%20store.%20They've%20walked%20into%20a%20local%20dollar%20store%20or%20pharmacy%20or%20department%20store%20and%20wondered%20whether%20there's%20been%20an%20explosion.%20Aisles%20are%20filled%20with%20unopened%20boxes%2C%20stacks%20of%20bins%2C%20and%20full%20dollies.%20Merchandise%20is%20strewn%20about.%20To%20get%20to%20the%20item%20on%20the%20shelf%20you%20actually%20want%2C%20you%20have%20to%20climb%20over%20a%20pile%20of%20crates.%20(If%20you%20have%20not%20had%20this%20experience%2C%20congratulations%2C%20and%20also%2C%20here%20are%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40yourviralfeed%2Fvideo%2F7195823999073455402%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40hilarious_scaless%2Fvideo%2F7386398922962603310%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evideos%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20at%20what%20I'm%20describing.)%20It's%20representative%20of%20the%20broader%20decline%20of%20the%20in-store%20retail%20experience.%20Stores%20are%20slashing%20costs%2C%20cutting%20corners%20at%20every%20turn%2C%20and%20generally%20ignoring%20the%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20cut%20costs%2C%20there's%20a%20very%20immediate%20and%20very%20visible%20impact%20to%20the%20bottom%20line.%20It's%20something%20that%20retailers%20do%2C%20and%20they're%20very%20happy%20to%20do%2C%20and%20investors%20are%20very%20comfortable%20with%20them%20doing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Neil%20Saunders%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20the%20retail%20consultancy%20GlobalData%2C%20said.%20Yes%2C%20they'll%20lose%20customers%20in%20the%20process%2C%20sales%20will%20fall%2C%20and%20loyalty%20will%20dissipate.%20But%20that's%20all%20subtle%20and%20harder%20to%20trace.%20%26quot%3BThey%20happen%20more%20slowly%20and%20steadily%20over%20a%20period%20of%20time%2C%20and%20they%20build%20up%20into%20a%20bigger%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20Saunders%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20that%20looks%20like%20on%20the%20ground%20is%20stores%20filled%20to%20the%20brim%20as%20boxes%20pile%20up.%20At%20Robyn's%20Dollar%20Tree%20stores%2C%20they%20can't%20call%20the%20distribution%20center%20and%20ask%20it%20to%20stop%20shipping%2C%20either%2C%20as%20everything%20continues%20to%20accumulate%20if%20they%20don't%20have%20time%20to%20put%20it%20away.%20%26quot%3BThe%20truck%20is%20going%20to%20show%20up%20whether%20you%20have%20room%20for%20it%20or%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20boxes-everywhere%20scenario%20used%20to%20be%20largely%20a%20dollar-%20or%20discount-store%20problem%2C%20but%20now%20the%20perilous%20piles%20have%20spread%20to%20other%20types%20of%20retailers.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20it's%20not%20just%20Dollar%20General%20anymore%20but%20also%20Target%20and%20Duane%20Reade.%20Much%20of%20the%20explanation%20is%20staffing%2C%20or%20rather%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20it.%20Many%20stores%20simply%20do%20not%20have%20enough%20people%20working%20to%20do%20everything%20necessary%2C%20between%20helping%20customers%20and%20stocking%20shelves%20and%20cleaning%20and%20fulfilling%20pickup%20and%20e-commerce%20orders.%20It's%20often%20the%20case%20that%20just%20one%20or%20two%20people%20are%20on%20a%20shift%20at%20a%20time%2C%20and%20checking%20customers%20out%20at%20the%20register%20takes%20precedence%2C%20meaning%20everything%20else%20falls%20by%20the%20wayside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20retail%20chains%20had%20to%20raise%20wages%20to%20compete%20for%20workers%20over%20the%20past%20several%20years%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20pandemic-induced%20labor%20shortage%20and%20as%20major%20retailers%20such%20as%20Amazon%20and%20Walmart%20upped%20their%20pay.%20One%20way%20some%20retailers%20have%20compensated%20is%20by%20reducing%20staffing.%20Maybe%20they%20now%20pay%20their%20workers%20%2415%20an%20hour%20instead%20of%20%2410%2C%20but%20where%20three%20people%20used%20to%20work%20a%20certain%20shift%2C%20there%20are%20now%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdding%20to%20the%20staffing%20problems%20is%20the%20simple%20lack%20of%20space.%20To%20keep%20their%20footprints%20small%20and%20their%20rent%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20low%2C%20many%20stores%20don't%20have%20much%20backroom%20area%20for%20storage.%20Long%20gone%20are%20the%20days%20of%20loading%20docks%20where%20stuff%20could%20sit%20until%20it%20was%20ready%20to%20be%20put%20out%2C%20said%20Jason%20Goldberg%2C%20the%20chief%20commerce%20strategy%20officer%20at%20Publicis%20Groupe%2C%20a%20global%20marketing%20firm.%20%26quot%3BMost%20stores%20are%20designed%20to%20have%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20merchandise%20out%20on%20the%20floor%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEssentially%2C%20this%20is%20an%20inventory%20issue%20and%20a%20labor%20issue.%20There's%20no%20stockroom%20for%20keeping%20products%20stowed%20away%20and%20nobody%20to%20unpack%20them%20when%20they%20arrive.%20Skeleton%20crews%20are%20doing%20their%20best%20to%20keep%20up%2C%20but%20they're%20constantly%20being%20squeezed.%20Shipping%20schedules%20are%20unpredictable.%20Customers%20are%20demanding.%20And%20the%20worse%20the%20job%20becomes%20%E2%80%94%20because%20the%20pay%20is%20low%2C%20because%20it's%20hard%20to%20get%20shifts%20%E2%80%94%20the%20more%20people%20quit%2C%20extending%20the%20cycle%20of%20doom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20what's%20happening%20at%20the%20Walgreens%20where%20Stephanie%20has%20worked%20in%20Florida%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%20When%20she%20started%2C%20there%20would%20be%20two%20cashiers%2C%20someone%20in%20photo%2C%20someone%20else%20in%20beauty%2C%20and%20two%20shift%20leads.%20They'd%20close%20the%20store%20with%20four%20or%20five%20people.%20Now%20when%20she's%20on%2C%20it's%20usually%20just%20her%20and%20another%20person%2C%20and%20they%20have%20to%20frantically%20try%20to%20get%20bins%20unloaded%20and%20put%20up%20sales%20tags%20all%20while%20working%20the%20register.%20They'll%20leave%20rolling%20carts%20around%20the%20store%20during%20the%20day%20to%20get%20to%20as%20they%20can%2C%20which%20is%20usually%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20shift.%20Bins%20can't%20be%20left%20out%20overnight.%20It's%20not%20a%20disaster%20zone%20%E2%80%94%20luckily%2C%20they%20do%20have%20some%20decent%20storage%20space%2C%20and%20the%20manager%20runs%20a%20tight%20ship%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20not%20perfect%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20basically%20cut%20a%20lot%20of%20positions%2C%20and%20now%20they%20work%20as%20minimum%20a%20staff%20as%20they%20can%2C%20and%20even%20with%20that%2C%20they're%20telling%20us%2C%20'You're%20over%20budget%2C%20we've%20got%20to%20cut%20more%20hours%2C'%26quot%3B%20Stephanie%2C%20also%20a%20pseudonym%2C%20said.%20She%20does%20DoorDash%20and%20Instacart%20on%20the%20side%2C%20so%20she%20also%20gets%20to%20experience%20the%20customer%20end%20of%20the%20equation%20when%20she%20runs%20to%20the%20dollar%20store%20to%20pick%20up%20orders%2C%20which%20is%20much%20worse%2C%20boxes-in-aisles-wise%2C%20than%20her%20Walgreens.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20even%20their%20fault.%20They%20have%20one%20worker%20on%20all%20the%20time%2C%20and%20they%20expect%20that%20worker%20to%20put%20their%20merchandise%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20reached%20for%20comment%20about%20this%20story%2C%20a%20Walgreens%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20the%20company%20is%20%26quot%3Balways%20working%20to%20improve%20our%20patient%20and%20customer%20experience%20by%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20our%20team%20members%20to%20do%20their%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGood%20managers%20are%20able%20to%20do%20some%20triage%2C%20which%20is%20why%20one%20store%20might%20be%20pretty%20picked%20up%20while%20others%20are%20a%20mess.%20But%20sometimes%2C%20constraints%20make%20it%20so%20it's%20impossible%20to%20keep%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20will%20be%20some%20store%20managers%20that%20have%20very%20strong%20operating%20disciplines%2C%20and%20they%20will%20not%20allow%20things%20to%20get%20out%20of%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20Saunders%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20there%20will%20be%20some%20store%20managers%20that%20are%20much%20more%20lax.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20easy%20as%20it%20is%20to%20point%20the%20finger%20at%20retailers%20for%20dropping%20the%20ball%20on%20inventories%20and%20aisles%2C%20they're%20not%20operating%20in%20a%20vacuum.%20They're%20in%20a%20landscape%20where%20margins%20are%20razor%20thin%2C%20e-commerce%20is%20cannibalizing%20their%20business%2C%20and%20consumers%20are%20hypersensitive%20to%20prices.%20One%20response%20for%20big-name%20retailers%2C%20including%20Walgreens%2C%20CVS%2C%20and%20Target%2C%20is%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpharmacy-cvs-walgreens-problems-desert-7-eleven-convenience-store-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshut%20down%20unprofitable%20locations%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20country.%20US%20retailers%20have%20announced%207%2C185%20store%20closures%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20research%20and%20advisory%20firm%20Coresight%2C%20up%20by%2058%20from%202023.%20(By%20comparison%2C%20they've%20announced%205%2C581%20store%20openings.)%20Among%20the%20stores%20that%20are%20staying%20open%2C%20retailers%20are%20super%20focused%20on%20maximizing%20their%20profitability%2C%20Claire%20Tassin%2C%20a%20retail%20and%20e-commerce%20analyst%20at%20Morning%20Consult%2C%20said.%20Staffing%20a%20store%20to%20have%20a%20pleasant%20customer%20experience%20isn't%20%26quot%3Bnecessarily%20in%20their%20budgets%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20message%20many%20retailers%20are%20getting%20from%20consumers%20is%20that%20the%20sacrifice%20on%20experience%20is%20acceptable%2C%20as%20long%20as%20they're%20keeping%20their%20prices%20low%2C%20especially%20for%20retailers%20where%20value%20is%20the%20main%20proposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYes%2C%20it's%20annoying%20when%20there's%20boxes%20in%20the%20aisles%20and%20it%20feels%20bad%20and%20cluttered%2C%20but%20if%20it's%20in%20the%20name%20of%20lowering%20costs%2C%20that%20is%20what%20consumers%20are%20signaling%20to%20these%20brands%20that%20they%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20Tassin%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20store's%20sort%20of%20primary%20purpose%20is%20value%20and%20convenience%2C%20that's%20what%20is%20going%20to%20matter%20most.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20there%20are%20limits.%20You%20trip%20over%20boxes%20in%20a%20store%20enough%20or%20wait%20endlessly%20for%20someone%20to%20unlock%20deodorant%20for%20you%2C%20and%20you'll%20probably%20give%20up%2C%20go%20somewhere%20else%2C%20or%20start%20looking%20online.%20For%20people%20with%20mobility%20issues%2C%20going%20to%20an%20overcrowded%20store%20isn't%20even%20an%20option.%20Retailers%20know%20people%20are%20shopping%20online%2C%20too%2C%20which%20is%20why%20the%20ones%20who%20are%20behind%20on%20e-commerce%20are%20trying%20to%20catch%20up%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20why%20the%20in-store%20experience%20is%20even%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20part%20of%20what's%20happening%20with%20Target%2C%20retail%20analysts%20told%20me.%20Despite%20the%20retailer's%20recent%20struggles%2C%20e-commerce%20has%20been%20a%20bright%20spot%20for%20it%2C%20Goldberg%20said.%20But%20part%20of%20the%20model%20is%20to%20use%20the%20space%20in%20the%20back%20of%20stores%20for%20goods%20that%20need%20to%20be%20shipped%20%E2%80%94%20space%20that%20previously%20would%20have%20been%20used%20for%20merchandise%20headed%20to%20the%20floor.%20%26quot%3BThey%20need%20space%20to%20stage%20orders%20and%20pack%20orders%20and%20hand%20orders%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20setup%20also%20loads%20up%20associates'%20duties%2C%20Saunders%20added.%20%26quot%3BThey%20pick%20orders%20for%20online%20delivery.%20They%20take%20them%20out%20to%20cars%20for%20curbside%20pickup.%20They%20have%20to%20man%20the%20desks%20where%20collections%20are%20made%20and%20then%20returns%20of%20online%20products%20are%20made%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20more%20tasks%20that%20now%20have%20to%20be%20done%20day-to-day%20in%20the%20store%2C%20and%20it's%20distracted%20and%20taken%20time%20away%20from%20some%20of%20the%20basics%20like%20merchandising.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Target%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company's%20staffing%20model%20accounts%20for%20online%20fulfillment%20being%20part%20of%20how%20it%20operates%20its%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dynamic%20is%20one%20of%20a%20race%20to%20the%20bottom%20that's%20turning%20into%20a%20race%20for%20survival.%20Retailers%20are%20stretching%20on%20pricing%20and%20staffing%20and%20quality%2C%20and%20eventually%2C%20something's%20got%20to%20give.%20But%20instead%20of%20trying%20to%20proactively%20make%20the%20in-store%20experience%20better%2C%20many%20continue%20to%20bury%20their%20heads%20in%20the%20sand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRather%20than%20thinking%2C%20'How%20can%20we%20differentiate%20ourselves%20to%20really%20attract%20shoppers%20to%20come%20to%20us%3F'%20They%20started%20competing%20head-on%20against%20online%20with%20price%20discounts%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sharmila%20Chatterjee%2C%20a%20senior%20lecturer%20in%20marketing%20at%20the%20MIT%20Sloan%20School%20of%20Management.%20%26quot%3BThe%20less%20you%20invest%20in%20in-store%20experience%2C%20the%20more%20the%20customers%20are%20turned%20off.%20So%20you%20are%20sort%20of%20pushing%20them%20away%2C%20to%20online.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EStuff%20spilling%20into%20aisles%20used%20to%20be%20a%20somewhat%20isolated%20problem%2C%20the%20sign%20of%20a%20particularly%20poorly%20run%20store.%20Increasingly%2C%20though%2C%20it's%20an%20everywhere%20problem.%20Some%20stores%20might%20be%20inspired%20to%20turn%20it%20around%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2024%2F07%2F11%2Fdollar-general-labor-department-settle-over-safety-violations.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eespecially%20after%20dollar%20stores%20have%20been%20hit%20with%20safety%20violations%20over%20blocked%20exits%2C%20crowded%20aisles%2C%20and%20clutter%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20but%20profit%20motive%20could%20prove%20a%20stronger%20incentive.%20Anecdotally%2C%20many%20consumers%20have%20noticed%20more%20piled%20boxes%20in%20more%20retailers%20lately%2C%20not%20fewer.%20And%20that's%20not%20just%20because%20it's%20the%20holidays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrowded%20walkways%20are%20a%20symptom%20of%20a%20much-bigger%20affliction%20hitting%20retail%2C%20which%20is%20that%20the%20business%20model%20isn't%20really%20working.%20Gone%20are%20the%20days%20when%20supercheap%20labor%20made%20adequate%20levels%20of%20store%20staffing%20easy%2C%20though%20I%20will%20note%20that%20Robyn%20makes%20just%20over%20%249%20an%20hour%20and%20Stephanie%20about%20%2415.50.%20Rents%20aren't%20going%20back%20to%20where%20they%20were.%20Consumers%20still%20do%20most%20of%20their%20shopping%20in%20person%2C%20but%20e-commerce%20is%20becoming%20more%20and%20more%20appealing%2C%20especially%20when%20brick%20and%20mortar%20is%20such%20a%20hassle.%20If%20it's%20no%20longer%20cheap%20or%20convenient%20to%20pop%20by%20the%20dollar%20store%20or%20drug%20store%2C%20what's%20the%20point%3F%20And%20there's%20always%20Walmart%2C%20which%20operationally%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20have%20this%20boxes-everywhere%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECynthia%2C%20another%20pseudonymous%20Dollar%20Tree%20worker%2C%20is%20at%20a%20store%20that%20opened%20about%20a%20month%20ago%20in%20Virginia.%20When%20she%20started%2C%20she%20thought%20it%20was%20weird%20that%20customers%20kept%20commenting%20on%20how%20clean%20and%20organized%20the%20place%20was.%20%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20compliments%20was%20that%20we%20can%20walk%20through%20the%20aisles.%20I%20was%20like%2C%20what%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20It's%20already%20starting%20to%20turn%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20%26quot%3Bno%20freaking%20way%26quot%3B%20she%20can%20get%20everything%20done%20in%20a%20shift%2C%20she%20said.%20Stuff's%20starting%20to%20pile%20up%2C%20and%20her%20coworkers%20are%20quitting%20because%20they're%20frustrated%20with%20the%20heavy%20workload%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThen%20it's%20more%20of%20that%20work%20falls%20on%20other%20people%20who%20already%20are%20burnt%20out%20and%20aggravated%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20nasty%20little%20cycle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstore-aisles-crowded-boxes-dollar-store-pharmacy-retail-apocalypse-shopping-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734341582000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675b3e8f57df667cc5a5dd70%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstore-aisles-crowded-boxes-dollar-store-pharmacy-retail-apocalypse-shopping-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22From%20Dollar%20Tree%20to%20Walgreens%20to%20Target%2C%20store%20aisles%20are%20filled%20with%20unpacked%20boxes%20and%20bins.%20It's%20a%20sign%20of%20deeper%20staffing%20problems.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A58%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fs