eriously%20%E2%80%94%20about%20the%20possibility%20that%20a%20new%20species%2Fkind%20of%20being%20might%20have%20interests%20of%20their%20own%20that%20matter%20morally%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforum.effectivealtruism.org%2Fposts%2FbvcbdnsJ9rEvmcZXn%2Fwhy-i-m-working-on-ai-welfare%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewrote%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20also%20a%20practical%20angle%3A%20taking%20the%20interests%20of%20AI%20systems%20seriously%20and%20treating%20them%20well%20could%20make%20it%20more%20likely%20that%20they%20return%20the%20favor%20if%2Fwhen%20they're%20more%20powerful%20than%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20might%20strike%20you%20as%20silly%2C%20or%20at%20least%20premature%2C%20to%20be%20thinking%20about%20the%20rights%20of%20robots%2C%20especially%20when%20human%20rights%20remain%20so%20fragile%20and%20incomplete.%20But%20Fish's%20new%20gig%20could%20be%20an%20inflection%20point%20in%20the%20rise%20of%20artificial%20intelligence.%20%26quot%3BAI%20welfare%26quot%3B%20is%20emerging%20as%20a%20serious%20field%20of%20study%2C%20and%20it's%20already%20grappling%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20thorny%20questions.%20Is%20it%20OK%20to%20order%20a%20machine%20to%20kill%20humans%3F%20What%20if%20the%20machine%20is%20racist%3F%20What%20if%20it%20declines%20to%20do%20the%20boring%20or%20dangerous%20tasks%20we%20built%20it%20to%20do%3F%20If%20a%20sentient%20AI%20can%20make%20a%20digital%20copy%20of%20itself%20in%20an%20instant%2C%20is%20deleting%20that%20copy%20murder%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20such%20questions%2C%20the%20pioneers%20of%20AI%20rights%20believe%20the%20clock%20is%20ticking.%20In%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2411.00986%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETaking%20AI%20Welfare%20Seriously%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20recent%20paper%20he%20coauthored%2C%20Fish%20and%20a%20bunch%20of%20AI%20thinkers%20from%20places%20like%20Stanford%20and%20Oxford%20argue%20that%20machine-learning%20algorithms%20are%20well%20on%20their%20way%20to%20having%20what%20Jeff%20Sebo%2C%20the%20paper's%20lead%20author%2C%20calls%20%26quot%3Bthe%20kinds%20of%20computational%20features%20associated%20with%20consciousness%20and%20agency.%26quot%3B%20In%20other%20words%2C%20these%20folks%20think%20the%20machines%20are%20getting%20more%20than%20smart.%20They're%20getting%20sentient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EPhilosophers%20and%20neuroscientists%20argue%20endlessly%20about%20what%2C%20exactly%2C%20constitutes%20sentience%2C%20much%20less%20how%20to%20measure%20it.%20And%20you%20can't%20just%20ask%20the%20AI%3B%20it%20might%20lie.%20But%20people%20generally%20agree%20that%20if%20something%20possesses%20consciousness%20and%20agency%2C%20it%20also%20has%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20the%20first%20time%20humans%20have%20reckoned%20with%20such%20stuff.%20After%20a%20couple%20of%20centuries%20of%20industrial%20agriculture%2C%20pretty%20much%20everyone%20now%20agrees%20that%20animal%20welfare%20is%20important%2C%20even%20if%20they%20disagree%20on%20how%20important%2C%20or%20which%20animals%20are%20worthy%20of%20consideration.%20Pigs%20are%20just%20as%20emotional%20and%20intelligent%20as%20dogs%2C%20but%20one%20of%20them%20gets%20to%20sleep%20on%20the%20bed%20and%20the%20other%20one%20gets%20turned%20into%20chops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20ahead%2010%20or%2020%20years%2C%20when%20AI%20systems%20have%20many%20more%20of%20the%20computational%20cognitive%20features%20associated%20with%20consciousness%20and%20sentience%2C%20you%20could%20imagine%20that%20similar%20debates%20are%20going%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sebo%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Mind%2C%20Ethics%2C%20and%20Policy%20at%20New%20York%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFish%20shares%20that%20belief.%20To%20him%2C%20the%20welfare%20of%20AI%20will%20soon%20be%20more%20important%20to%20human%20welfare%20than%20things%20like%20child%20nutrition%20and%20fighting%20climate%20change.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20plausible%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20has%20written%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20within%201-2%20decades%20AI%20welfare%20surpasses%20animal%20welfare%20and%20global%20health%20and%20development%20in%20importance%2Fscale%20purely%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20near-term%20wellbeing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20my%20money%2C%20it's%20kind%20of%20strange%20that%20the%20people%20who%20care%20the%20most%20about%20AI%20welfare%20are%20the%20same%20people%20who%20are%20most%20terrified%20that%20AI%20is%20getting%20too%20big%20for%20its%20britches.%20Anthropic%2C%20which%20casts%20itself%20as%20an%20AI%20company%20that's%20concerned%20about%20the%20risks%20posed%20by%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20partially%20funded%20the%20paper%20by%20Sebo's%20team.%20On%20that%20paper%2C%20Fish%20reported%20getting%20funded%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Effective%20Altruism%2C%20part%20of%20a%20tangled%20network%20of%20groups%20that%20are%20obsessed%20with%20the%20%26quot%3Bexistential%20risk%26quot%3B%20posed%20by%20rogue%20AIs.%20That%20includes%20people%20like%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20who%20says%20he's%20racing%20to%20get%20some%20of%20us%20to%20Mars%20before%20humanity%20is%20wiped%20out%20by%20an%20army%20of%20sentient%20Terminators%2C%20or%20some%20other%20extinction-level%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20there's%20a%20paradox%20at%20play%20here.%20The%20proponents%20of%20AI%20say%20we%20should%20use%20it%20to%20relieve%20humans%20of%20all%20sorts%20of%20drudgery.%20Yet%20they%20also%20warn%20that%20we%20need%20to%20be%20nice%20to%20AI%2C%20because%20it%20might%20be%20immoral%20%E2%80%94%20and%20dangerous%20%E2%80%94%20to%20hurt%20a%20robot's%20feelings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20AI%20community%20is%20trying%20to%20have%20it%20both%20ways%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Mildred%20Cho%2C%20a%20pediatrician%20at%20the%20Stanford%20Center%20for%20Biomedical%20Ethics.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20an%20argument%20that%20the%20very%20reason%20we%20should%20use%20AI%20to%20do%20tasks%20that%20humans%20are%20doing%20is%20that%20AI%20doesn't%20get%20bored%2C%20AI%20doesn't%20get%20tired%2C%20it%20doesn't%20have%20feelings%2C%20it%20doesn't%20need%20to%20eat.%20And%20now%20these%20folks%20are%20saying%2C%20well%2C%20maybe%20it%20has%20rights%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20here's%20another%20irony%20in%20the%20robot-welfare%20movement%3A%20Worrying%20about%20the%20future%20rights%20of%20AI%20feels%20a%20bit%20precious%20when%20AI%20is%20already%20trampling%20on%20the%20rights%20of%20humans.%20The%20technology%20of%20today%2C%20right%20now%2C%20is%20being%20used%20to%20do%20things%20like%20deny%20healthcare%20to%20dying%20children%2C%20spread%20disinformation%20across%20social%20networks%2C%20and%20guide%20missile-equipped%20combat%20drones.%20Some%20experts%20wonder%20why%20Anthropic%20is%20defending%20the%20robots%2C%20rather%20than%20protecting%20the%20people%20they're%20designed%20to%20serve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Anthropic%20%E2%80%94%20not%20a%20random%20philosopher%20or%20researcher%2C%20but%20Anthropic%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%20wants%20us%20to%20take%20AI%20welfare%20seriously%2C%20show%20us%20you're%20taking%20human%20welfare%20seriously%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Lisa%20Messeri%2C%20a%20Yale%20anthropologist%20who%20studies%20scientists%20and%20technologists.%20%26quot%3BPush%20a%20news%20cycle%20around%20all%20the%20people%20you're%20hiring%20who%20are%20specifically%20thinking%20about%20the%20welfare%20of%20all%20the%20people%20who%20we%20know%20are%20being%20disproportionately%20impacted%20by%20algorithmically%20generated%20data%20products.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESebo%20says%20he%20thinks%20AI%20research%20can%20protect%20robots%20and%20humans%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20%26quot%3BI%20definitely%20would%20never%2C%20ever%20want%20to%20distract%20from%20the%20really%20important%20issues%20that%20AI%20companies%20are%20rightly%20being%20pressured%20to%20address%20for%20human%20welfare%2C%20rights%2C%20and%20justice%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20think%20we%20have%20the%20capacity%20to%20think%20about%20AI%20welfare%20while%20doing%20more%20on%20those%20other%20issues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESkeptics%20of%20AI%20welfare%20are%20also%20posing%20another%20interesting%20question%3A%20If%20AI%20has%20rights%2C%20shouldn't%20we%20also%20talk%20about%20its%20obligations%3F%20%26quot%3BThe%20part%20I%20think%20they're%20missing%20is%20that%20when%20you%20talk%20about%20moral%20agency%2C%20you%20also%20have%20to%20talk%20about%20responsibility%2C%26quot%3B%20Cho%20says.%20%26quot%3BNot%20just%20the%20responsibilities%20of%20the%20AI%20systems%20as%20part%20of%20the%20moral%20equation%2C%20but%20also%20of%20the%20people%20that%20develop%20the%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20build%20the%20robots%3B%20that%20means%20they%20have%20a%20duty%20of%20care%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20robots%20don't%20harm%20people.%20What%20if%20the%20responsible%20approach%20is%20to%20build%20them%20differently%20%E2%80%94%20or%20stop%20building%20them%20altogether%3F%20%26quot%3BThe%20bottom%20line%2C%26quot%3B%20Cho%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20that%20they're%20still%20machines.%26quot%3B%20It%20never%20seems%20to%20occur%20to%20the%20folks%20at%20companies%20like%20Anthropic%20that%20if%20an%20AI%20is%20hurting%20people%2C%20or%20people%20are%20hurting%20an%20AI%2C%20they%20can%20just%20turn%20the%20thing%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fadam-rogers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAdam%20Rogers%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweirdest-job-ai-anthropic-hired-employee-care-chatbots-emotions-welfare-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734339782000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674f93c5e45a68623a27af76%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweirdest-job-ai-anthropic-hired-employee-care-chatbots-emotions-welfare-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Anthropic%20is%20tending%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bwelfare%26quot%3B%20of%20AI%20bots%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0before%20they%20grow%20up%20and%20turn%20on%20us%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22arogers%40businessinsider.com%20(Adam%20Rogers)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A84%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweirdest-job-ai-anthropic-hired-employee-care-chatbots-emotions-welfare-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Cloud%20security%20startup%20Wiz%20turned%20down%20a%20Google%20takeover.%20Now%2C%20it%20plans%20to%20ride%20the%20AI%20boom%20to%20an%20IPO.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223712%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Raaz%20Herzberg%2C%20CMO%20at%20Wiz.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6758717e91c1cc343d47a6fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222475%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERaaz%20Herzberg%2C%20CMO%20and%20VP%20of%20product%20strategy%20at%20Wiz.%3Cp%3EElla%20Barak%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECloud%20security%20startup%20Wiz%20has%20grown%20rapidly%20in%20just%20four%20years%2C%20raising%20%241.9%20billion%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20AI%20boom%20has%20accelerated%20cloud%20adoption%2C%20says%20Raaz%20Herzberg%2C%20the%20CMO%20of%20Wiz.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWiz%20rejected%20a%20%2423%20billion%20Google%20acquisition%20offer%20in%20July%20and%20said%20it%20plans%20to%20IPO%20instead.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%202020%2C%20Raaz%20Herzberg%20was%20a%20product%20manager%20at%20Microsoft%20Azure%20when%20she%20was%20offered%20a%20position%20at%20Wiz%2C%20a%20newly%20created%20cloud%20security%20startup.%20Since%20then%2C%20Wiz%20has%20turned%20down%20a%20%2423%20billion%20takeover%20offer%20from%20Google%2C%20expanded%20into%20Europe%2C%20and%20reached%20%24500%20million%20in%20annual%20recurring%20revenue.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20next%20priority%20is%20to%20double%20that%20revenue%20metric%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20become%20a%20public%20company.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWiz%20was%20launched%20by%20four%20cofounders%20who%20sold%20their%20previous%20business%2C%20Adallom%2C%20to%20Microsoft.%20It%20bills%20itself%20as%20a%20cloud%20security%20company%20that%20helps%20companies%20identify%20risks%20in%20their%20cloud%20providers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20felt%20like%20an%20opportunity%20I%20couldn't%20possibly%20pass%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Herzberg%2C%20now%20the%20chief%20marketing%20officer%20and%20vice%20president%20of%20product%20strategy%20at%20Wiz%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview%20from%20the%20company's%20new%20London%20office.%20%26quot%3BI%20started%20as%20head%20of%20product%20%E2%80%94%20but%20we%20started%20in%20the%20worst%20time.%20This%20was%20March%202020%2C%20when%20COVID-19%20started%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20easy%20to%20remember%20because%20everything%20changed%20immediately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turned%20out%20that%20the%20pandemic%20was%20a%20boon%20for%20business.%20As%20more%20companies%20shifted%20to%20remote%20work%2C%20they%20increasingly%20relied%20on%20cloud%20services%20%E2%80%94%20expanding%20Wiz's%20client%20base.%20Four%20years%20since%20its%20launch%2C%20the%20scaleup%20has%20raised%20over%20%241.9%20billion%20in%20funding%20from%20investing%20heavyweights%20such%20as%20Andreessen%20Horowitz%2C%20Thrive%20Capital%2C%20and%20Index%20Ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20now%20sees%20huge%20opportunities%20to%20use%20the%20AI%20boom%20to%20cement%20its%20position%20in%20the%20market%20before%20it%20launches%20its%20initial%20public%20offering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2288ce0ead-09c9-4296-aefc-85e75721eebf%5C%22%3EAI%20adoption%20has%20supercharged%20Wiz's%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECloud%20computing%20offers%20crucial%20infrastructure%20underpinning%20AI%20applications.%20As%20more%20companies%20rush%20to%20adopt%20AI%2C%20security%20and%20privacy%20have%20taken%20center%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20adoption%20of%20AI%20is%20very%20similar%20to%20what%20happened%20with%20the%20accelerated%20use%20of%20cloud%2C%26quot%3B%20Herzberg%20said.%20Wiz%20has%20found%20that%20over%2080%25%20of%20its%20customers%20are%20using%20AI%20services%20%E2%80%94%20which%20%26quot%3Bare%2C%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20like%20cloud%20services.%20Companies%20don't%20buy%20their%20machines%20or%20chips%2C%20so%20they're%20using%20these%20technologies%20on%20the%20cloud%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPart%20of%20the%20reason%20we're%20growing%20so%20fast%20is%20because%20we%20have%20access%20to%20the%20public%20cloud%2C%20which%20is%20growing%20incredibly%20fast%20%E2%80%94%20and%20AI%20only%20pushes%20that%20growth%20further%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20AI%20services%20are%20often%20used%20on%20public%20clouds%20%E2%80%94%20a%20service%20offered%20by%20third%20parties%20rather%20than%20an%20internal%20network%20%E2%80%94%20cloud%20security%20has%20become%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsecurity-threats-ai-models-rise-new-startups-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecritical%20issue%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWiz's%20rapid%20growth%20has%20also%20been%20bolstered%20by%20its%20arsenal%20of%20acquisitions.%20This%20year%2C%20it%20scooped%20up%20security%20startups%20Rafft%2C%20Gem%2C%20and%20Dazz%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20bulk%20up%20its%20engineering%20talent%20and%20product%20suite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20acquire%20companies%2C%20we%20don't%20sell%20their%20product.%20They%20rebuild%20it%20from%20scratch%20in%20the%20Wiz%20infrastructure%2C%26quot%3B%20Herzberg%20told%20BI%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20company%20is%20still%20on%20the%20hunt%20for%20more%20acquisitions.%20%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20in%20this%20concept%20of%20growing%20inorganically.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ec1d3d39-0712-4662-87f2-c577b4e75a98%5C%22%3EEuropean%20expansion%20on%20the%20road%20to%20IPO%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWiz's%20global%20headquarters%20is%20in%20New%20York%2C%20with%20offices%20in%20Virginia%2C%20Texas%2C%20Colorado%2C%20and%20Israel.%20In%20August%202024%2C%20Wiz%20established%20its%20European%20headquarters%20in%20London.%20Its%20plush%20office%20is%20a%20short%20walk%20from%20Silicon%20Roundabout%20%E2%80%94%20London's%20scaled-down%20answer%20to%20Silicon%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20European%20market%20has%20been%20an%20ideal%20fit%20for%20our%20technology%20because%20it's%20more%20constrained%20by%20security%2C%20and%20more%20privacy%20aware%20than%20the%20US%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20Herzberg%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BWe%20estimate%20we%20will%20be%20able%20to%20get%2035%25%20of%20our%20revenue%20from%20Europe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWiz%20works%20with%20industry%20heavyweights%20on%20the%20continent%2C%20such%20as%20Revolut%2C%20Tide%2C%20and%20BMW.%20In%202024%2C%20it%20says%20it%20reached%20%24500%20million%20in%20ARR%20%E2%80%94%20but%20is%20aiming%20to%20reach%20%241%20billion%20before%20it%20IPOs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOperating%20independently%20is%20a%20big%20priority%20for%20the%20company.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20Wiz%20turned%20down%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwiz-turns-down-23-billion-deal-google-ipo-independent-public-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2423%20billion%20offer%20from%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20instead%20opting%20to%20prime%20itself%20for%20a%20public%20debut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHerzberg%20declined%20to%20comment%20about%20the%20Google%20deal%20but%20added%20that%20Wiz%20had%20lofty%20ambitions%20to%20establish%20itself%20as%20a%20market%20leader%20in%20the%20cloud%20security%20domain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20building%20a%20company%20that%20I%20believe%20can%20be%20the%20biggest%20cybersecurity%20company%20in%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20at%20this%20point%20we%20are%20on%20that%20path.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20likened%20companies%20buying%20security%20services%20to%20buying%20insurance%20packages%2C%20pointing%20to%20incumbents%20in%20the%20security%20industry%20with%20a%20similar%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20if%20I%20look%20at%20the%20wing%20of%2C%20for%20example%2C%20network%20security%20firewalls%2C%20it%20has%20a%20clear%20leader%20%E2%80%94%20people%20today%20buy%20Palo%20Alto%20firewalls.%20They%20used%20to%20buy%20checkpoint%20firewalls.%20Now%20the%20leader%20is%20Palo%20Alto%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnother%20example%20would%20be%20like%20the%20endpoint%20production%20server%20protection%2C%20that's%20a%20big%20domain%20on%20its%20own%2C%20and%20then%20it%20has%20a%20clear%20leader%2C%20like%20CrowdStrike.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20public%20cloud%20domain%20balloons%2C%20Herzberg%20believed%20there%20needs%20to%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bleader%20in%20place%20to%20protect%20that%20domain%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20adding%20that%20Wiz%20had%20a%20goal%20of%20taking%20that%20mantle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e35fc032-11cc-4ea6-a292-bbe033b41cfe%5C%22%3EGrowth%20ambitions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20slate%20of%20elections%20this%20year%20has%20pushed%20the%20company%20to%20prepare%20for%20more%20government-mandated%20cybersecurity%20measures%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20US.%20In%20anticipation%20of%20Donald%20Trump's%20second%20term%2C%20Wiz%20has%20started%20building%20on%20a%20federal%20sales%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Herzberg%20said%20the%20scaleup%20is%20in%20%26quot%3Bno%20rush%26quot%3B%20to%20go%20public.%20It's%20now%20looking%20for%20a%20chief%20finance%20officer%2C%20a%20requirement%20for%20companies%20that%20want%2