n%20leaves%20behind%20a%20legacy%20of%20laughter%2C%20charm%2C%20and%20grace.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Factress-jill-jacobson-known-for-star-trek-and-falcon-crest-passes-away-at-70%2Farticleshow%2F116362937.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BBalraj%20Sahni%20Was%20Arrested...%26quot%3B%3A%20N%20Sitharaman%20vs%20M%20Kharge%20Over%20Constitution%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EStarting%20the%20debate%20to%20mark%20the%20Constitution's%2075th%20anniversary%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20Finance%20Minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20launched%20an%20all-out%20attack%20on%20the%20Congress%20and%20accused%20it%20of%20repeatedly%20trying%20to%20undermine%20the%20Constitution%20through%20amendments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETargeting%20the%20country's%20first%20Prime%20Minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20she%20referred%20to%20the%20first%20Constitutional%20amendment%20in%201951.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20essentially%20to%20curb%20the%20freedom%20of%20speech%20(and%20expression).%20India%20prides%20itself%20even%20today%20on%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression.%20But%20the%20first%20interim%20government%20came%20up%20with%20a%20Constitutional%20amendment%20to%20curb%20the%20freedom%20of%20speech%20of%20Indians.%20That%20is%20because%20the%20first%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20this%20country%20deplored%20press%20scrutiny%20of%20his%20government%20even%20as%20he%20publicly%20praised%20freedom%20of%20press%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20during%20the%20debate%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Defence%20Minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%20had%20slammed%20Congress%20for%20the%20multiple%20Constitutional%20amendments%20during%20its%20rule.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Sitharaman%20also%20referred%20to%20the%20arrest%20of%20poet-lyricist%20Majrooh%20Sultanpuri%20and%20actor%20Balraj%20Sahni%20in%201949.%20%26quot%3BDuring%20one%20of%20the%20meetings%20organised%20for%20mill%20workers%2C%20Majrooh%20Sultanpuri%20recited%20a%20poem%20that%20was%20written%20against%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru.%20Therefore%2C%20he%20had%20to%20go%20to%20jail.%20He%20refused%20to%20render%20an%20apology%20and%20was%20jailed%20along%20with%20Balraj%20Sahni%2C%20an%20eminent%20actor%20of%20those%20days.%20That%20is%20the%20level%20of%20tolerance%20and%20today%20we%20hold%20the%20Constitution%20in%20our%20hand%20and%20say%20freedom%20of%20speech%2C%20there%20is%20a%20sense%20of%20fear%20in%20our%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20taking%20a%20swipe%20at%20Congress%20leader's%20Constitution%20pitch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Finance%20Minister%20said%20the%20Congress%20government%20banned%20a%20book%2C%20Nehru%3A%20A%20Political%20Biography%2C%20by%20Michael%20Edwardes%20and%20a%20film%2C%20Kissa%20Kursi%20Ka%2C%20in%201975%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20it%20questioned%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20her%20son%20and%20also%20the%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%20Minister%20then%26quot%3B.%20In%201988%2C%20she%20said%2C%20Salman%20Rushdie's%20book%20The%20Satanic%20Verses%20was%20banned.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20this%20spree%20of%20curtailing%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%2C%20containing%20freedom%20of%20press%20happened%20before%201949%20and%20continues%20after%201951%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amendments%20brought%20by%20Congress%20governments%2C%20Ms%20Sitharaman%20said%2C%20were%20not%20aimed%20at%20strengthening%20democracy%20but%20to%20shield%20those%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Finance%20Minister%20said%20that%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Second%20World%20War%2C%20over%2050%20countries%20became%20independent%20and%20framed%20their%20Constitution.%20But%20while%20many%20of%20them%20have%20changed%20it%20completely%2C%20India's%20Constitution%20has%20stood%20the%20test%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%20we%20are%20extremely%20proud%20of%20the%20way%20India's%20democracy%20is%20growing.%20Iit%20is%20time%20to%20reaffirm%20our%20commitment%20to%20build%20India%2C%20that%20is%20Bharat%2C%20that%20shall%20uphold%20the%20spirit%20enshrined%20in%20this%20sacred%20document%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Sitharaman%20also%20referred%20to%20amendments%20brought%20in%20to%20nullify%20an%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%20judgment%20in%201975%20against%20Indira%20Gandhi%20in%20an%20election%20malpractices%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDuring%20the%20pendency%20of%20this%20case%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20Congress%20enacted%20the%2039th%20Constitutional%20Amendment%20Act%20in%201975%20which%20added%20Article%20392%20(A)%20to%20the%20Constitution%20which%20says%20that%20elections%20to%20the%20President%2C%20Vice%20President%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20Lok%20Sabha%20Speaker%20cannot%20be%20challenged%20in%20any%20court%20in%20the%20country%20and%20it%20can%20be%20done%20only%20before%20a%20parliamentary%20committee.%20Imagine%20that%20for%20a%20person%20to%20save%20her%20chair%2C%20an%20amendment%20was%20made%20even%20before%20the%20court%20judgment%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Finance%20Minister%20also%20referred%20to%20the%20Shah%20Bano%20case%20during%20Rajiv%20Gandhi's%20term%20as%20Prime%20Minister.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20the%20judgment%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20Shah%20Bano%20case%2C%20the%20Congress%20(government)%20passed%20the%20Muslim%20Women%20Protection%20of%20Rights%20on%20Divorce%20Act%201986%20which%20denied%20Muslim%20women%20their%20right%20to%20alimony%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20the%20imposition%20of%20the%20Emergency%20in%201975%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20amendments%20were%20not%20about%20strengthening%20democracy%20but%20protecting%20those%20in%20power.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Congress%20chief%20and%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20said%20the%20BJP%20has%20never%20respected%20the%20Constitution%20or%20the%20national%20flag%20and%20stressed%20that%20there%20is%20a%20danger%20to%20the%20Constitution%20under%20this%20government.%20Referring%20to%20the%20situation%20in%20Bangladesh%20after%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20ouster%2C%20he%20said%2C%C2%A0%E2%80%9COur%20brave%20leader%20Indira%20Gandhi%20divided%20Pakistan%20into%20two%20parts%20and%20liberated%20Bangladesh...%20The%20pride%20of%20this%20country%20spread%20across%20the%20world.%20The%20chaos%20that%20is%20going%20on%20there%20(in%20Bangladesh)%2C%20at%20least%20these%20(BJP)%20people%20should%20open%20their%20eyes%20and%20try%20to%20save%20the%20minorities%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20veteran%20leader%20said%20the%20BJP%20never%20fought%20for%20the%20country.%20%26quot%3BHow%20can%20such%20people%20talk%20about%20Nehru.%20We%20need%20to%20introspect%20deeply.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20clear%20from%20the%20debates%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20that%20erstwhile%20leaders%20of%20RSS%20were%20against%20the%20Constitution.%20Those%20who%20hated%20the%20flag%2C%20Ashok%20Chakra%20and%20the%20Constitution%20are%20today%20teaching%20lessons%20to%20us%20on%20the%20Constitution%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0Prime%20Minister%20Modi%2C%20he%20said%2C%20should%20apologise%20to%20the%20people%20of%20the%20country%20for%20misleading%20them%20by%20%26quot%3Btwisting%26quot%3B%20Prime%20Minister%20Nehru's%20letter%20to%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734339180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F2v7a9u6o_sitharaman-kharge_625x300_16_December_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fconstitution-debate-nirmala-sitharaman-n-sitharamans-balraj-sahni-example-to-slam-congress-in-constitution-debate-7259344%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Starting%20the%20debate%20to%20mark%20the%20Constitution's%2075th%20anniversary%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20Finance%20Minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20launched%20an%20all-out%20attack%20on%20the%20Congress%20and%20accused%20it%20of%20repeatedly%20trying%20to%20undermine%20the%20Constitution%20through%20amendments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fconstitution-debate-nirmala-sitharaman-n-sitharamans-balraj-sahni-example-to-slam-congress-in-constitution-debate-7259344%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bavarian%20Nordic%20partners%20with%20Serum%20Institute%20for%20Mpox%20vaccine%20production%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734339152000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbavarian-nordic-partners-with-serum-institute-for-mpox-vaccine-production-124121600527_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bavarian%20Nordic%20has%20partnered%20with%20the%20Serum%20Institute%20of%20India%20to%20produce%20its%20Mpox%20vaccine%20for%20the%20Indian%20market%20and%20expand%20global%20capacity%20through%20contract%20manufacturing%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%2014%20Years%20On%2C%20The%20Arab%20Spring%20Morphs%20Into%20An%20Islamic%20Winter%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fo71hn8s_syria_625x300_09_December_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2017%2C%202010%2C%20Mohammed%20Bouazizi%2C%20a%20Tunisian%20fruit%20vendor%2C%20set%20himself%20on%20fire%20to%20protest%20against%20local%20officials%20having%20confiscated%20his%20stall.%20His%20act%20ignited%20the%20flames%20of%20a%20pan-Arab%20anti-establishment%20mass%20uprising%20that%20came%20to%20be%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98Arab%20Spring'.%20On%20the%20eve%20of%20the%2014th%20anniversary%20of%20that%20incident%20and%20in%20the%20backdrop%20of%20last%20fortnight's%20coup%20in%20Syria%E2%80%94the%20Arab%20Spring's%20longest-running%20and%20bloodiest%20manifestation%E2%80%94an%20analysis%20of%20this%20rare%20phenomenon%20is%20called%20for.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETunisia%20To%20Egypt%20To%20Libya%2C%20The%20All-Encompassing%20Revolution%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2014%20years%2C%20the%20Arab%20Spring%20has%20jolted%20several%20Arab%20countries%2C%20although%20its%20net%20impact%20remains%20contentious.%20Bouazizi's%20self-immolation%20spurred%20mass%20demonstrations%20in%20Tunisia%2C%20toppling%2C%20within%20a%20month%2C%20the%20autocratic%20President%20in%20power%20for%2023%20years.%20Egypt%20followed%20shortly%20thereafter%3A%20the%20mass%20demonstrations%20centred%20on%20Cairo's%20Tahrir%20Square%20forced%20President%20Mubarak%20to%20leave%20after%2018%20days%20despite%20having%20tried%20all%20sorts%20of%20deflections%20to%20stay%20in%20power.%20He%20was%20in%20power%20for%2032%20years%20and%20was%20replaced%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Military%20Council%2C%20which%20eventually%20gave%20way%20to%20the%20country's%20first%20democratically%20held%20elections.%20The%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%20government%20lasted%20only%20a%20few%20months%20and%20was%20overthrown%20by%20the%20Army%2C%20which%20continues%20to%20wield%20power%20even%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECol%20Muammar%20Qadhafi%2C%20President%20for%2042%20years%20of%20oil-rich%20Libya%2C%20also%20faced%20anti-government%20protests%20from%20mid-February%202011%2C%20which%20soon%20morphed%20into%20an%20armed%20insurrection%20based%20in%20the%20eastern%20coastal%20city%20of%20Benghazi.%20A%20UN%20Security%20Council%20Resolution%20authorising%20%E2%80%9Call%20necessary%20measures%E2%80%9D%20to%20protect%20civilians%20was%20weaponised%20by%2027%20Western%20and%20Middle%20Eastern%20powers%20to%20launch%20intensive%20airstrikes%20against%20the%20pro-Qadhafi%20forces.%20This%20tilted%20the%20balance%20against%20the%20government%20forces%20and%20eventually%20led%20to%20President%20Qadhafi%20being%20killed%20in%20combat%20on%20October%2020.%20Even%20after%20massive%20bloodletting%20since%2C%20the%20civil%20war%20has%20continued%20and%20the%20country%20is%20still%20split%2C%20with%20a%20government%20each%20in%20Tripoli%20and%20Benghazi.%20Libya%20was%20the%20first%20case%20of%20foreign%20interests%20being%20strongly%20involved%20in%20influencing%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20Arab%20Spring%3B%20it%20was%20not%20to%20be%20the%20last.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20protests%20in%20Bahrain%20that%20began%20in%20February%202011%20were%20partly%20spurred%20by%20a%20Shia%20majority%20population%20chafing%20under%20a%20Sunni%20monarchy.%20These%20were%20initially%20aimed%20at%20achieving%20greater%20political%20freedom%20and%20respect%20for%20human%20rights%2C%20but%20the%20repression%20by%20authorities%20pushed%20them%20in%20that%20direction.%20The%20fellow%20monarchies%20of%20the%20Gulf%20Cooperation%20Council%20were%20alarmed%20by%20the%20perceived%20involvement%20of%20Iran%20and%20Hezbollah%20in%20disrupting%20the%20smallest%20Gulf%20state%20and%20intervened%20militarily%20to%20quell%20the%20protests.%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20the%20UAE%20sought%20to%20nip%20similar%20protests%20and%20reform%20movements%20in%20the%20bud%20with%20strongarm%20tactics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECivil%20Wars%20In%20Syria%20And%20Yemen%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArab%20Spring%20protests%20in%20Syria%20and%20Yemen%2C%20two%20ethnically%20diverse%20and%20politically%20frozen%20republics%20under%20dynastic%20rules%2C%20unlocked%20long-suppressed%20popular%20sub-national%20aspirations.%20The%20confrontation%20did%20not%20remain%20peaceful%20for%20long%2C%20each%20morphing%20into%20a%20bitter%20civil%20war%20that%20brought%20in%20neighbouring%20and%20global%20powers%20resulting%20in%20counterproductive%20outcomes.%20In%20Syria%2C%20a%20country%20of%2023%20million%2C%2013%20years%20of%20civil%20war%20caused%20the%20deaths%20of%20nearly%20half%20a%20million%20people%2C%20displacement%20of%20nearly%2015%20million%20both%20internally%20and%20externally%2C%20and%20destruction%20put%20at%20half%20a%20trillion%20dollars.%20Yemen%20continued%20to%20be%20split%20into%20the%20al-Houthis-run%20north%20and%20the%20UN-recognised%20coalition%20in%20the%20south%E2%80%94both%20joined%20at%20the%20hip%20by%20disease%20and%20malnutrition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20complicated%20precedents%2C%20the%20second%20wave%20of%20Arab%20Spring%20unfurled%202018%20onwards%20in%20Algeria%2C%20Sudan%2C%20Lebanon%20and%20Iraq.%20While%20all%20of%20them%20had%20reforms%20as%20their%20leitmotif%2C%20the%20demands%20were%20more%20local%20and%20focused%3A%20in%20Algeria%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EHerak%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20agitation%20was%20aimed%20at%20thwarting%20President%20Bouteflika%2C%20in%20power%20for%2019%20years%2C%20seeking%20a%20fresh%20term%20despite%20his%20physical%20incapacity.%20The%20Sudanese%20agitated%20against%20the%2032%20years%20of%20corrupt%20and%20violent%20rule%20of%20a%20military%20dictator.%20Iraqi%20and%20Lebanese%20youth%20wanted%20to%20bring%20down%20%3Cem%3EMuhasasa%20Taifiyeh%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20system%20of%20sectarian%20power-sharing.%20While%20this%20wave%20of%20Arab%20Springers%20did%20partially%20achieve%20their%20immediate%20objectives%2C%20all%20of%20them%20are%20still%20mired%20in%20their%20respective%20crises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20these%20two%20waves%2C%20the%20Arab%20Spring%20touched%20almost%20all%20parts%20of%20the%20Arab%20World%E2%80%94from%20Western%20Sahara%20to%20Jordan%20and%20Kuwait.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20New%20Genre%20Of%20Dissent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20not%20to%20over-contextualise%20the%20Arab%20Spring.%20Even%20before%202011%2C%20the%20Arab%20world%20had%20similar%20protest%20movements%2C%20most%20prominent%20among%20these%20being%20the%20bread%20riots%20in%20Egypt%20and%20Algeria%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Palestinian%20Intefadah%20from%20the%20mid-1980s%20onwards.%20However%2C%20two%20decades%20later%2C%20the%20Arab%20Spring%20was%20a%20new%20dissent%20genre%E2%80%94being%20wild-fired%20by%20the%20spread%20of%20satellite%20television%20and%20social%20media%20leap-frogging%20over%20the%20state%20controls.%20Secondly%2C%20such%20protests%20also%20took%20place%20in%20other%20non-Arab%20but%20Islamic%20countries%20such%20as%20Iran%20(Hijab%20Protests)%2C%20Pakistan%20(Imran%20Khan%20detention)%20and%20recently%20in%20Bangladesh%20(Prime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20ouster)%2C%20with%20mixed%20results.%20Even%20Israel%2C%20a%20regional%20exception%2C%20has%20had%20recurring%20mass%20protests%20against%20government%20attempts%20to%20curb%20judicial%20powers%20and%20to%20bring%20Israeli%20hostages%20home%20from%20Hamas%20captivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20foregone%20helps%20us%20to%20identify%20the%20root%20causes%20of%20the%20Arab%20Spring.%20Among%20them%2C%20the%20most%20widely%20felt%20reason%20could%20be%20a%20sense%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EHogra%3C%2Fem%3E'%2C%20a%20Maghrebi%20Arabic%20word%20roughly%20equivalent%20to%20the%20powerful's%20contempt%20for%20a%20commoner%3B%20it%20could%20be%20expanded%20to%20envelope%20oppressive%20governance%2C%20personality%20cults%20and%20pretentious%20demagogy%20quite%20common%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20When%20coupled%20with%20stagnant%2C%20non-inclusive%20and%20non-representative%20polity%2C%20it%20manifests%20the%20Nasser-era%20paradigm%20of%20the%20ruled-adulating-the-benign-dictator%20that%20got%20increasingly%20out%20of%20place%20with%20the%20ethos%20of%20urbanised%2C%20better-educated%20and%20more%20aspirational%20modern%20Arab%20societies.%20The%20demographic%20reasons%20came%20next%3A%20the%20youth%20bulging%20to%20the%20working%20age%20found%20few%20worthwhile%20jobs%20within%20the%20country%20and%20faced%20shrinking%20opportunities%20for%20employment%20and%20migration%20abroad%20due%20to%20the%20global%20recession%20and%20low%20oil%20prices.%20These%20frustrations%20were%20aggravated%20by%20corruption%20and%20the%20skewed%20wealth%20distribution.%20Lastly%2C%20the%20average%20citizen%20was%20far%20younger%20than%20the%20long-ruling%20gerontocrats%20causing%20political%20disconnect%20and%20alienation.%20The%20boiling%20cauldron%20of%20public%20angst%20suddenly%20and%20conveniently%20cascaded%20into%20the%20Arab%20Spring.%20The%20top%20echelons'%20recourse%20to%20police%20terror%20and%2For%20palliatives%20was%20insufficient%20to%20contain%20the%20outpouring%2C%20and%20the%20shiny%20but%20brittle%20state%20cracked%20under%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20The%20Revolution%20Failed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20logical%20to%20ask%20why%2C%20despite%20initial%20success%2C%20the%20Arab%20Spring%20almost%20universally%20failed%20to%20reform%20the%20system.%20There%20are%20several%20reasons%20to%20be%20cited%20for%20this%20letdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20the%20Arab%20Spring%20movements%20were%20initially%20largely%20spontaneous%20without%20any%20leadership%20or%20agenda.%20Their%20initial%20aim%20was%20limited%20to%20a%20change%20at%20the%20top.%20Once%20that%20was%20achieved%2C%20they%20had%20little%20clue%20and%20unity%20on%20how%20to%20put%20in%20a%20better%20structure%20replacement%20as%20all%20of%20the%20Arab%20world%20governance%20models%20were%20flawed.%20Secondly%2C%20the%20long%20oppressive%20rule%20had%20meant%20that%20there%20was%20no%20credible%20%E2%80%9Cloyal%20opposition%E2%80%9D%E2%80%94and%20the%20void%20was%20filled%20by%20either%20the%20Islamists%20(who%20often%20ran%20a%20mosque-based%20clandestine%20network)%20or%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThirdly%2C%20foreign%20interventions%20often%20muddied%20the%20waters%3A%20they%20dithered%20between%20propping%20up%20the%20status%20quo%20or%20backing%20the%20democratic%20aspirations.%20The%20Western%20Powers%2C%20quite%20possessive%20about%20this%20eco-strategic%20region%2C%20also%20played%20their%20games%2C%20particularly%20in%20oil-rich%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFourthly%2C%20the%20whirling%20anarchy%20often%20beckoned%20Islamic%20terrorism%20to%20hijack%20the%20agenda%E2%80%94as%20al-Qaeda%20and%20Islamic%20State%20did.%20Last%2C%20but%20not%20least%2C%20the%20national%20borders%20straddling%20ethnic%20and%20tribal%20groups%20also%20cross-pollinated%20the%20Arab%20Spring.%20The%20result%20was%20often%20a%20free-for-all%2C%20in%20which%20the%20most%20organised%20and%20committed%20side%20often%20won%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhither%20The%20Arab%20World%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20Arab%20Spring's%2014th%20anniversary%2C%20it%20is%20natural%20to%20ask%20if%20the%20Arab%20world%20is%20any%20better%20today%20and%20what%20its%20long-term%20impact%20is%20going%20to%20be.%20As%20of%20now%2C%20the%20most%20tangible%20takeaway%20from%20the%20Arab%20Spring%20is%20that%20a%20lasting%20socio-political%20transformation%20cannot%20be%20stillborn%E2%80%94it%20needs%20to%20evolve%20organically.%20One%20can%20also%20venture%20to%20suggest%20that%20the%20Arab%20Spring%20experience%20has%20no%20clear%20victors%20so%20far%E2%80%94at%20least%20the%20masses%20who%20are%20not%20only%20duped%C2%A0politically%20but%20also%20materially%20worse%20off.%20For%20instance%2C%20during%20the%20first%20decade%20of%20the%20Arab%20Spring%20to%202021%2C%20the%20nominal%20per%20capita%20income%20of%20an%20average%20Syrian%20declined%20by%2086%25%2C%20from%20%242971%20to%20%24421.%20So%2C%20although%20the%20al-Assad%20regime%20is%20finally%20gone%2013%20years%20after%20Arab%20Springers%20first%20demanded%20its%20ouster%2C%20the%20epic%20death%20and%20destruction%20make%20it%20a%20pyrrhic%20victory.%20Moreover%2C%20there%20is%20no%20guarantee%20that%20the%20succeeding%20Hay'at%20Tahrir%20al-Sham%20(HTS)-led%20Salafi%20Sunni%20coalition%20would%20be%20an%20improvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20that%20one%20can%20safely%20say%20at%20this%20stage%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20Arab%20Spring%20phenomenon%20is%20that%20it%20has%20shown%20a%20harsh%20mirror%20to%20the%20various%20stakeholders%20and%20made%20them%20aware%20of%20the%20limits%20of%20their%20respective%20powers.%20While%20one%20wishes%20that%20this%20awareness%20helps%20them%20to%20shift%20socio-political%20dynamics%20towards%20greater%20moderation%20and%20mutual%20accommodation%2C%20evidence%20on%20the%20ground%20suggests%20such%20hope%20may%20remain%20an%20ever-receding%20desert%20mirage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(The%20author%20is%20a%20retired%20Indian%20Ambassador%20who%20learnt%20the%20Arabic%20language%20in%20Damascus.%20He%20currently%20heads%20Eco-Diplomacy%20and%20Strategies%2C%20a%20Delhi-based%20consultancy.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734337800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fo71hn8s_syria_625x300_09_December_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2F14-years-on-the-arab-spring-morphs-into-an-islamic-winter-7259671%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22All%20that%20one%20can%20safely%20say%20at%20this%20stage%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20Arab%20Spring%20phenomenon%20is%20that%20it%20has%20shown%20a%20harsh%20mirror%20to%20the%20various%20stakeholders%20and%20made%20them%20aware%20of%20the%20limits%20of%20their%20respective%20powers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2F14-years-on-the-arab-spring-morphs-into-an-islamic-winter-7259671%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampU