oats%20to%20Soy%20Wax%20Candles%3A%204%20Eco-Friendly%20Innovations%20From%20Northeast%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ECreativity%20and%20innovation%20play%20a%20major%20role%20in%20solving%20challenges%20and%20improving%20lives%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20a%20simple%2C%20low-technology%20cold%20storage%20unit%20or%20soy%20wax%20candles%20held%20in%20beautiful%20pottery%20jars.%20India%E2%80%99s%20ranking%20in%20the%20Global%20Innovation%20Index%20(GII)%20has%20improved%20consistently%20over%20the%20years%2C%20and%C2%A0in%202024%2C%20it%20ranked%2039th%20out%20of%20133%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20we%20describe%20four%20interesting%20innovative%20ventures%20from%20Northeast%20India%2C%20known%20for%20its%20rich%20biodiversity%20and%20culture.%20They%20range%20from%20the%20simple%20to%20the%20sophisticated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20ventures%20are%20featured%20in%20the%20book%20%E2%80%98People%E2%80%99s%20Festival%20of%20Innovations%20%E2%80%93%202023%E2%80%99.%20The%20festival%20was%20jointly%20organised%20by%20GIAN%20(Grassroots%20Innovations%20Augmentation%20Network)%2C%20Ahmedabad%2C%20founded%20by%20Prof%20Anil%20Gupta%2C%20and%20C-CAMP%20(Centre%20for%20Cellular%20and%20Molecular%20Platforms).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E1.%20Scented%20soy%20wax%20candles%20in%20Longpi%20jars%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ancient%20craft%20of%20Longpi%20black%20pottery%20has%20been%20given%20a%20modern%20twist%20by%20the%20Manipur-based%20venture%20%E2%80%98October%20Pumpkin%2C%E2%80%99%20which%20uses%20these%20handcrafted%20jars%20for%20scented%20soy%20wax%20candles.%20Soy%20wax%2C%20a%20renewable%20and%20biodegradable%20plant-based%20product%2C%20stands%20out%20for%20its%20eco-friendly%20properties%2C%20unlike%20paraffin%20wax%2C%20which%20emits%20harmful%20toxins.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20venture%20has%20been%20selected%20by%20BITS%20Pilani%20for%20Rs%2015%20lakh%20funding%20under%20the%20%E2%80%98Womenpreneur%20for%20Bharat%202.0%20program%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-4-1733814775.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rinchon%20Kashung%20and%20Aleks%20Vashum%20sell%20scented%20soy%20wax%20candles%20in%20traditional%20Longpi%20jars%20through%20their%20venture%20'October%20Pumpkin'.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-4-1733814775.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-4-1733814775-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-4-1733814775-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-4-1733814775-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-4-1733814775-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-388002%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ERinchon%20Kashung%20and%20Aleks%20Vashum%20sell%20scented%20soy%20wax%20candles%20in%20traditional%20Longpi%20jars%20through%20their%20venture%20%E2%80%98October%20Pumpkin%E2%80%99%3B%20Image%20courtesy%3A%20October%20Pumpkin%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLongpi%20pottery%20is%20a%20traditional%20craft%20practised%20by%20the%20Tangkhul%20tribal%20community%20in%20Manipur%E2%80%99s%20Ukhrul%20district%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Rinchon%20Kashung%2C%20co-founder%20of%20October%20Pumpkin.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20made%20from%20a%20unique%20paste%20of%20ground%20serpentine%20stone%20and%20brown%20clay%2C%20both%20found%20exclusively%20in%20this%20region.%20The%20pots%20are%20crafted%20by%20hand%2C%20sun-dried%2C%20and%20then%20fired.%20They%20are%20polished%20with%20pine%20leaves%20to%20achieve%20their%20distinctive%20sheen.%20Unlike%20other%20pottery%2C%20this%20process%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20use%20a%20wheel%2C%20making%20it%20highly%20labour-intensive.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERinchon%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20Aleks%20Vashum%2C%20founded%20October%20Pumpkin%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed%20wp-block-embed-youtube%20wp-embed-aspect-16-9%20wp-has-aspect-ratio%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed__wrapper%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20data-skipgform_ajax_framebjll%20data-origheight%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fq_RtLvooMLc%3Fenablejsapi%3D1%26rel%3D0%26modestbranding%3D0%26autoplay%3D0%26cc_load_policy%3D0%26iv_load_policy%3D3%26loop%3D0%26fs%3D1%26playsinline%3D1%26controls%3D1%26color%3Dred%26cc_lang_pref%3D%26autohide%3D2%26theme%3Ddark%26%5C%22%20data-no-lazy%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20player%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20data-origwidth%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20sold%20over%207%2C500%20units%20across%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Rinchon%2C%20a%20first-generation%20entrepreneur%20from%20the%20Tangkhul%20tribe.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20learned%20the%20art%20of%20pottery-making%20myself.%20Each%20Longpi%20jar%20takes%20about%20a%20week%20to%20craft%2C%20with%20round%20and%20cylindrical%20shapes%20being%20the%20most%20popular%20for%20candles.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20mission%20goes%20beyond%20selling%20products.%20%E2%80%9CI%20aim%20to%20promote%20sustainability%20while%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F357751%2Ftraditional-clay-utensils-dattatreya-vyas-swadeshi-blessings-rajasthan-cookware-kitchenware-shark-tank%2F%5C%22%3Ecreating%20employment%20opportunities%20for%20the%20artisans%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20make%20these%20jars%2C%20especially%20women.%20So%20far%2C%20we%20have%20impacted%20300%20artisans%20from%20Longpi%20village%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20brand%20name%20%E2%80%98October%20Pumpkin%E2%80%99%20has%20a%20personal%20touch.%20%E2%80%9CI%20wanted%20a%20name%20that%20felt%20close%20to%20my%20heart.%20I%20was%20born%20in%20October%2C%20and%20pumpkin%20happens%20to%20be%20my%20favourite%20vegetable%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Rinchon%20with%20a%20laugh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733814988.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rinchon%20with%20the%20Longpi%20jars%20containing%20soy%20wax%20candles.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733814988.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733814988-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733814988-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733814988-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733814988-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-388009%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ERinchon%20with%20the%20Longpi%20jars%20containing%20soy%20wax%20candles%3B%20Image%20courtesy%3A%20October%20Pumpkin%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoy%20wax%20candles%20burn%2050%20percent%20slower%20than%20paraffin%20wax%20candles%2C%20making%20them%20more%20cost-effective%20despite%20being%20slightly%20pricier.%20The%20soy%20wax%20used%20is%20sourced%20from%20Gujarat%2C%20where%20purified%20soybean%20oil%20undergoes%20hydrogenation%20%E2%80%94%20a%20process%20that%20introduces%20hydrogen%20to%20convert%20the%20liquid%20oil%20into%20solid%20wax.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMany%20candles%20in%20the%20Indian%20market%20suffer%20from%20%E2%80%98candle%20tunnelling%2C%E2%80%99%20where%20the%20wax%20burns%20unevenly%2C%20leaving%20a%20circular%20pit%20around%20the%20wick%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%20%E2%80%9COur%20candles%20are%20thoroughly%20tested%20to%20prevent%20this%20issue%2C%20and%20we%20also%20educate%20customers%20on%20proper%20burning%20techniques.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20our%20scents%20are%20crafted%20using%20fragrance%20oils%20that%20are%20rigorously%20tested%20and%20sourced%20from%20companies%20committed%20to%20using%20non-toxic%20chemicals%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20oils%20are%20blended%20into%20the%20wax%20at%20a%20precise%20temperature.%20Each%20scent%20is%20designed%20to%20evoke%20specific%20emotions%20and%20experiences.%20For%20instance%2C%20some%20of%20our%20popular%20ones%20include%20%E2%80%98Forest%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98Walk%20Around%20the%20Bakery%2C%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98In%20the%20Library.%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20She%20adds%20with%20a%20smile%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%98In%20the%20Library%E2%80%99%20even%20captures%20the%20nostalgic%20scent%20of%20old%20books!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed%20wp-block-embed-youtube%20wp-embed-aspect-16-9%20wp-has-aspect-ratio%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed__wrapper%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F7A-kBnADm-8%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%223%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22281%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20faced%20challenges%20such%20as%20courier%20transportation%20glitches%20and%20packaging%20issues.%20They%20pack%20their%20candles%20in%20Longpi%20jars%20using%20eco-friendly%20materials%20like%20paper%20and%20cardboard%20boxes.%20Large%20Longpi%20jar%20candles%2C%20containing%20approximately%201%20kg%20of%20soy%20wax%2C%20are%20priced%20at%20around%20Rs%203%2C500.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOctober%20Pumpkin%20has%20also%20participated%20in%20two%20pop-up%20stalls%20at%20Nagaland%20House%2C%20New%20Delhi%2C%20under%20%E2%80%98Home%20%26amp%3B%20Heart%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20a%20collective%20of%20Northeast%20women%20entrepreneurs%20based%20in%20the%20national%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E2.%20Zero-energy%20low-cost%20cold%20storage%20units%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarmers%20in%20Meghalaya%E2%80%99s%20West%20Khasi%20Hills%20struggle%20with%20warehousing%2C%20storage%2C%20and%20logistics.%20The%20lack%20of%20affordable%2C%20energy-efficient%20storage%20solutions%20for%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%20often%20results%20in%20significant%20post-harvest%20losses%20and%20reduced%20incomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20small%20project%20can%20make%20a%20big%20difference%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Binolin%20Syiemlieh%2C%20centre%20manager%20at%20the%20Nongstoin%20Social%20Service%20Society%20(NSSS)%2C%20the%20non-profit%20driving%20this%20innovation.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20set%20up%20simple%2C%20small-scale%2C%20zero-energy%20storage%20units%20near%20farmers%E2%80%99%20fields%20to%20preserve%20their%20produce.%20So%20far%2C%20three%20units%20have%20been%20constructed%20in%20different%20villages%2C%20each%20costing%20Rs%201.64%20lakh.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20NSSS%20works%20for%20the%20welfare%20of%20the%20community%20in%20several%20areas%20like%20farming%2C%20mental%20health%2C%20and%20child%20services.%20I%20am%20involved%20in%20projects%20for%20farmers.%20I%20mobilise%20farmers%20and%20also%20help%20them%20access%20assistance%20from%20government%20and%20private%20agencies%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20idea%20for%20these%20storage%20units%20came%20from%20the%20farmers%20themselves.%20Struggling%20to%20store%20their%20produce%2C%20they%20faced%20losses%20even%20before%20reaching%20the%20markets%2C%20compounded%20by%20low%20prices.%20While%20the%20project%20began%20in%202019%2C%20its%20progress%20was%20delayed%20due%20to%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENSSS%20oversees%20the%20construction%20of%20these%20units%20by%20hiring%20contractors%2C%20using%20locally%20available%20materials%20like%20burned%20bricks%2C%20river%20sand%2C%20bamboo%20poles%2C%20CGI%20sheets%2C%20iron%20nails%2C%20cement%2C%20and%20pebbles.%20Each%20unit%20can%20store%20up%20to%20a%20tonne%20of%20produce%2C%20preserving%20it%20for%20one%20to%20four%20weeks.%20Remarkably%2C%20the%20units%20are%20quick%20to%20construct%20%E2%80%94%20taking%20just%20a%20day%20or%20two%20%E2%80%94%20and%20require%20no%20maintenance.%20Farmers%20can%20use%20them%20free%20of%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20fill%20the%20gap%20between%20two%20layers%20of%20the%20structure%20with%20river%20sand%20and%20pebbles.%20This%20sand%20is%20watered%20twice%20a%20day.%20This%20keeps%20the%20produce%20cool.%20Each%20unit%20benefits%20over%20120%20farmers%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Binolin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-5-1733815262.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Binolin%20Syiemlieh%2C%20centre%20manager%20at%20the%20Nongstoin%20Social%20Service%20Society%20(NSSS)%2C%20says%20their%20non-profit%20has%20set%20up%20simple%2C%20small-scale%2C%20zero-energy%20storage%20units%20near%20farmers%E2%80%99%20fields%20to%20preserve%20their%20produce.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-5-1733815262.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-5-1733815262-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-5-1733815262-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-5-1733815262-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-5-1733815262-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-388012%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EBinolin%20Syiemlieh%2C%20centre%20manager%20at%20the%20Nongstoin%20Social%20Service%20Society%20(NSSS)%2C%20says%20their%20non-profit%20has%20set%20up%20simple%2C%20small-scale%2C%20zero-energy%20storage%20units%20near%20farmers%E2%80%99%20fields%20to%20preserve%20their%20produce%3B%20Image%20courtesy%3A%20Nongstoin%20Social%20Service%20Society%20(NSSS)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20cold%20storage%20units%2C%20though%20rooted%20in%20scientific%20principles%2C%20involve%20no%20elaborate%20technology.%20They%20are%20managed%20by%20the%20Village%20Executive%20Committee%20(VEC)%2C%20ensuring%20equitable%20access%20for%20all%20villagers%20while%20keeping%20produce%20clean%20and%20fresh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20project%20is%20funded%20by%20the%20Meghalaya%20Basin%20Management%20Agency%20(MBMA)%2C%20a%20not-for-profit%20organisation%20handling%20externally%20aided%20government%20projects.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20initiative%20is%20supported%20by%20the%20World%20Bank%20under%20an%20innovation%20fund%20that%20helps%20improve%20or%20scale%20up%20solutions.%20It%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Community-Led%20Landscape%20Management%20Project%2C%20which%20focuses%20on%20addressing%20natural%20resource%20management%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Wankit%20Swer%2C%20general%20manager%20at%20MBMA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20farmers%20are%20smallholders%20with%20limited%20production.%20After%20meeting%20their%20own%20needs%2C%20the%20excess%20is%20sold.%20Without%20proper%20storage%2C%20they%20often%20resort%20to%20distress%20sales%20of%20perishable%20items.%20These%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F314446%2Fchennai-student-eco-friendly-tech-increases-produce-shelf-life-sunharvested-coolrooms%2F%5C%22%3Ecold%20storage%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%20prevent%20such%20sales%20and%20provide%20a%20better%20solution%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E3.%20Anti-microbial%20fabric%20made%20from%20banana%20fibre%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENagaland-based%20venture%20Hengna%20%26amp%3B%20Maben%20Private%20Limited%20is%20making%20remarkable%20progress%20in%20harnessing%20banana%20fibre.%20%E2%80%9COur%20banana%20fibre%20project%20is%20part%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Runway%20India%E2%80%99%20division%20of%20our%20company%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Major%20Tanay%20Maben%2C%20co-founder%20of%20the%20venture.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20currently%20in%20the%20research%20and%20development%20(R%26amp%3BD)%20phase%2C%20working%20on%20producing%20fabric%20from%20banana%20fibre%2C%20which%20boasts%20anti-microbial%20properties.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20anti-microbial%20properties%20of%20banana%20fibre%2C%20derived%20from%20natural%20compounds%20in%20the%20plant%2C%20create%20a%20protective%20shield%20on%20the%20fabric%2C%20inhibiting%20the%20growth%20of%20bacteria%20and%20fungi.%20This%20fabric%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20used%20in%20medical%20textiles%2C%20and%20efforts%20are%20underway%20to%20integrate%20additional%20functional%20properties%2C%20such%20as%20water%20resistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-9-1733816042.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nengneithem%20Hengna%20(L)%20and%20Major%20Tanay%20Maben%20(R)%20-%20co-founders%20of%20Hengna%20%26amp%3B%20Maben%20Private%20Limited%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-9-1733816042.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-9-1733816042-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-9-1733816042-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-9-1733816042-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-9-1733816042-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-388032%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ENengneithem%20Hengna%20(L)%20and%20Major%20Tanay%20Maben%20(R)%20%E2%80%93%20co-founders%20of%20Hengna%20%26amp%3B%20Maben%20Private%20Limited%3B%20Image%20courtesy%3A%20Hengna%20%26amp%3B%20Maben%20Private%20Limited%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F354933%2Fombak-sustainable-furniture-shruthi-prakash-rattan-chairs-table-wall-decor-from-banana-fibres-in-indonesia-india%2F%5C%22%3EBanana%20fibre%20is%20also%20an%20eco-friendly%20alternative%20to%20polymer-based%20fabrics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20it%20is%20biodegradable.%20Moreover%2C%20banana%20plants%20require%20minimal%20water%20and%20chemical%20inputs%2C%20including%20pesticides%20and%20fertilisers%2C%20making%20them%20a%20sustainable%20option%20compared%20to%20water-intensive%20cotton%2C%20explains%20Major%20Tanay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20the%20company%20produces%20handicrafts%20and%20packaging%20materials%20using%20banana%20fibre.%20With%20the%20goal%20of%20establishing%20banana%20fibre%20as%20a%20signature%20product%20of%20Nagaland%2C%20it%20has%20trained%20700%20artisans%20across%20Nagaland%20and%20other%20Northeast%20Indian%20states%20to%20create%20handmade%20items%20from%20the%20fibre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed%20wp-block-embed-youtube%20wp-embed-aspect-16-9%20wp-has-aspect-ratio%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed__wrapper%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fho_0vUAs4-w%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22281%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20founder%2C%20Nengneithem%20Hengna%2C%20who%20brings%2013%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20the%20handicrafts%20sector%2C%20began%20working%20with%20banana%20fibre%20in%202019.%20She%20experimented%20with%20different%20grades%20of%20fibre%2C%20braiding%20techniques%2C%20and%20stitching%20methods.%20She%20met%20Major%20Maben%20during%20COVID%20relief%20efforts%2C%20and%20they%20discovered%20shared%20goals.%20This%20collaboration%20led%20to%20the%20official%20incorporation%20of%20the%20company%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBanana%20is%20a%20zero-waste%20cash%20crop%20which%20yields%20a%20variety%20of%20products%20and%20by-products%20within%20a%20year%20of%20planting.%20It%20grows%20well%20in%20gently%20sloping%20terrain%20and%20is%20low-maintenance.%20Also%2C%20banana%20fibre%20is%20a%20very%20versatile%20fibre%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Major%20Tanay.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20coarser%20type%20can%20be%20used%20to%20make%20coasters%20while%20the%20delicate%20variety%20can%20be%20used%20to%20craft%20jewellery%20and%20hair%20extensions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-6-1733816156.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Trained%20artisans%20across%20Nagaland%20and%20other%20Northeast%20Indian%20states%20create%20handmade%20items%20from%20banana%20fibre.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-6-1733816156.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-6-1733816156-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-6-1733816156-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-6-1733816156-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-6-1733816156-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-388038%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ETrained%20artisans%20across%20Nagaland%20and%20other%20Northeast%20Indian%20states%20create%20handmade%20items%20from%20banana%20fibre%3B%20Image%20courtesy%3A%20Hengna%20%26amp%3B%20Maben%20Private%20Limited%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20banana%20%E2%80%98pseudostem%E2%80%99%20is%20passed%20through%20rollers%20(like%20in%20the%20case%20of%20sugarcane)%20and%20the%20mulch%20is%20extracted.%20What%20remains%20is%20the%20fibre%2C%20which%20is%20washed%2C%20dried%2C%20segregated%2C%20combed%20(to%20get%20various%20grades)%20and%20graded%2C%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20products%20made%20and%20sold%20by%20the%20company%20using%20banana%20fibre%20and%20bark%20are%20vases%2C%20planters%2C%20jewellery%2C%20bags%2C%20clutches%2C%20coasters%2C%20table%20mats%2C%20wall%20hangings%2C%20lanterns%20and%20baskets.%20The%20prices%20of%20these%20products%20range%20from%20Rs%20300%20to