0gradually%20inspiring%20others%20to%20join%20his%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20remarkable%20success%20stories%20came%20from%20the%20village%20of%20Pingali-Kd%2C%20located%20just%20five%20kilometres%20from%20Dahiwadi.%20Initially%2C%20the%20village%20showed%20little%20interest%20in%20Abhay%E2%80%99s%20water%20conservation%20efforts.%20%E2%80%9CAt%20first%2C%20only%208-10%20people%20were%20interested%2C%E2%80%9D%20Abhay%20recalls.%20But%20instead%20of%20giving%20up%2C%20Abhay%20invited%2025%20children%20with%20disabilities%20to%20participate%20in%20rallies%2C%20focusing%20on%20Shramdaan%20(labour%20donation).%20These%20rallies%20soon%20captured%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20entire%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20villagers%2C%20Sujata%20Waghmare%2C%20admits%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20Abhay%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%20first%20introduced%20the%20water%20conservation%20project%20in%20our%20village%2C%20I%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20really%20interested.%20But%20when%20he%20asked%20me%20to%20attend%20the%20training%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20give%20it%20a%20try.%20The%20training%20was%20so%20impactful%20that%20I%20immediately%20realised%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20part%20of%20this%20cause.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAbhay%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%20brought%20so%20much%20energy%20and%20enthusiasm%20to%20the%20project%20that%20it%20felt%20like%20it%20was%20his%20village.%20His%20passion%20motivated%20me%20to%20get%20actively%20involved%2C%20attending%20meetings%20and%20joining%20the%20projects.%20I%20also%20encouraged%20others%20to%20take%20part%20so%20they%20could%20understand%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F332290%2Fmaharashtra-water-scarcity-drought-prone-jalna-district-gets-aid-water-bodies-desilted%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimportance%20of%20water%20conservation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20What%20amazed%20me%20most%20was%20that%20even%20though%20Abhay%20sir%20is%20physically%20disabled%2C%20his%20drive%20to%20work%20is%20beyond%20inspiring%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20villagers%20became%20engaged%2C%20Pingali-Kd%20raised%20the%20necessary%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F247233%2Fbori-bandh-check-dam-ajay-sharma-sewa-welfare-society-khunti-jharkhand-water-shortage-water-conservation-agriculture-volunteer-work-him16%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efunds%20to%20build%20dams%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Within%20a%20short%20time%2C%20the%20village%20overcame%20its%20water%20scarcity%20issues%2C%20and%20even%20began%20supplying%20water%20to%20neighbouring%20villages.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBapu%20Kambale%20from%20Pingali-Kd%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20a%20mechanic%2C%20and%20I%20know%20Abhay%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%20through%20Art%20of%20Living%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Water%20conservation%20has%20always%20been%20close%20to%20my%20heart%2C%20as%20we%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20the%20devastating%20effects%20of%20drought.%20There%20was%20a%20time%20when%20we%20had%20to%20walk%20up%20to%20seven%20kilometres%20just%20to%20fetch%20water.%20Our%20wells%20were%20dry%2C%20and%20finding%20drinking%20water%20was%20a%20constant%20struggle.%20With%20such%20a%20shortage%2C%20we%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20even%20think%20of%20farming.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20Abhay%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%20began%20his%20work%20on%20water%20conservation%20in%20our%20village%2C%20I%20joined%20him.%20We%20built%20dams%2C%20and%20Abhay%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%20took%20the%20lead%20in%20raising%20funds.%20He%20stayed%20in%20our%20village%20for%20nearly%2040%20days%2C%20overseeing%20the%20progress%20and%20ensuring%20everything%20was%20done%20properly%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%20with%20deep%20appreciation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20boy%20diagnosed%20with%20polio%20to%20a%20man%20leading%20a%20movement%20for%20water%20conservation%20across%20villages%2C%20Abhay%20Todkar%E2%80%99s%20journey%20is%20a%20source%20of%20hope%20for%20others%20facing%20similar%20challenges.%20His%20story%20proves%20that%20no%20limitation%20can%20hold%20back%20the%20human%20spirit%20when%20fuelled%20by%20grit%20and%20a%20passion%20for%20serving%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Arunava%20Banerjee%3B%20All%20photos%20courtesy%20Abhay%20Todkar%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733754600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-12-01-at-22.12.46-1-1733487498.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D387316%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Abhay%20Todkar%2C%20a%2044-year-old%20from%20drought-prone%20Dahiwadi%20village%20defied%20the%20odds%20of%20living%20with%20polio%20to%20lead%20a%20remarkable%20water%20conservation%20movement.%20His%20efforts%20have%20brought%20sustainable%20change%20to%2064%20villages%2C%20turning%20struggles%20into%20triumphs%20through%20determination%20and%20community-driven%20initiatives.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Raajwrita%20Dutta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F387316%2Fabhay-todkar-dahiwadi-polio-water-conservation-movement-across-villages-maharashtra%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%221%20Woman%E2%80%99s%20Magazine%20Is%20Challenging%20What%20It%20Means%20To%20Be%20a%20Child%20Born%20in%20a%20Red-Light%20Area%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20were%20little%20and%20the%20police%20would%20raid%20our%20houses%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%2C%20we%E2%80%99d%20see%20people%20jumping%20over%20walls%20and%20running%20away.%20My%20grandmother%20would%20wake%20up%20all%20the%20children%20in%20the%20house%2C%20gather%20us%20together%2C%20and%20tell%20us%20to%20read%20out%20loud%2C%20so%20the%20police%20would%20know%20that%20school-going%2C%20regular%20children%20lived%20there.%20I%20always%20found%20this%20so%20strange.%20Why%20were%20we%20constantly%20told%20to%20hide%2C%20to%20run%3F%20What%20crime%20had%20we%20committed%20that%20made%20us%20feel%20that%20our%20existence%20was%20dishonest%3F%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Naseema%20Khatoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaseema%2C%2039%2C%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20a%20red-light%20area%2C%20experiencing%20firsthand%20the%20stigma%20and%20neglect%20faced%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F350204%2Fsandhya-nair-kranti-ngo-daughters-of-sex-workers-kamathipura-international-university%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esex%20workers%20and%20their%20children%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Today%2C%20having%20broken%20free%20from%20the%20cycle%20of%20poverty%2C%20she%20has%20become%20a%20powerful%20voice%20for%20the%20marginalised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20when%20I%20was%20enrolled%20in%20school%20that%20I%20developed%20a%20sense%20of%20inquisitiveness%20about%20my%20identity.%20I%20would%20be%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20in%20an%20environment%20where%20people%20would%20ask%20me%20my%20full%20name%20and%20where%20I%20was%20from.%20But%20I%20was%20told%20not%20to%20tell%20people%20where%20I%20lived%2C%E2%80%9D%20Naseema%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELife%20in%20a%20red-light%20district%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaseema%E2%80%99s%20home%20was%20Chaturbhuj%20Sthan%2C%20a%20red-light%20district%20in%20Muzaffarpur%2C%20Bihar.%20Named%20after%20a%20Vishnu%20temple%2C%20the%20area%20has%20historically%20been%20home%20to%20sex%20workers%20and%20%3Cem%3Etawaifs%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20its%20religious%20name%20does%20not%20shield%20the%20community%20from%20societal%20stigma.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20should%20I%20not%20tell%20people%20who%20I%20am%20and%20where%20I%20come%20from%3F%E2%80%9D%20Naseema%20remembers%20asking%20her%20father%2C%20who%20quickly%20shut%20her%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20girls%20from%20school%20would%20all%20walk%20home%20together%2C%20but%20they%20would%20take%20a%20long%20wounded%20route%20to%20avoid%20my%20%3Cem%3Egully%3C%2Fem%3E.%20They%20were%20told%20to%2C%20so%20I%E2%80%99d%20go%20alone%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20child%2C%20Naseema%20was%20a%20witness%20to%20frequent%20police%20raids%20in%20her%20neighbourhood.%20These%20experiences%20left%20a%20lasting%20impact%2C%20and%20it%20was%20during%20this%20time%20that%20she%20began%20to%20fully%20understand%20the%20marginalisation%20her%20community%20faced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-500x500.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20image%20of%20Naseema%20Khatoon%20who%20is%20a%20human%20rights%20activist%20and%20a%20part%20of%20the%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20(NHRC)%20advisory%20group%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-500x500.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-300x300.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-150x150.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-768x768.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-600x600.jpg%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-400x400.jpg%20400w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-200x200.jpg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818-96x96.jpg%2096w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu1-1733397818.jpg%20773w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-386775%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENaseema%20is%20a%20human%20rights%20activist%20and%20a%20part%20of%20the%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20(NHRC)%20advisory%20group%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20constant%20fear%20of%20the%20police%2C%20the%20forced%20hiding%2C%20and%20the%20need%20to%20constantly%20run%20were%20not%20just%20external%20pressures%3B%20they%20profoundly%20shaped%20her%20self-perception%20and%20her%20struggle%20to%20define%20her%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20hard%20to%20define%20yourself%20as%20a%20daughter%20of%20a%20red-light%20area%20and%20not%20a%20sex%20worker.%20This%20is%20a%20concept%20that%20is%20unheard%20of%20to%20the%20outside%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20But%20Naseema%20never%20let%20go%20of%20her%20desire%20to%20define%20herself%20beyond%20what%20the%20world%20forced%20on%20her.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CJust%20as%20someone%20who%20has%20a%20small%20vegetable%20stall%20that%20he%20pushes%20around%20on%20the%20road%2C%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20want%20their%20child%20to%20continue%20doing%20the%20same%20work%20they%20do%2C%20a%20sex%20worker%20also%20does%20not%20want%20their%20child%20to%20continue%20to%20do%20the%20same.%20She%20wants%20better%20for%20her%20kids%2C%E2%80%9D%20Naseema%20reflects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98I%20was%20always%20so%20scared%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201995%2C%20when%20Naseema%20was%20a%20young%20teen%2C%20IAS%20Rajbala%20Verma%2C%20who%20was%20posted%20as%20a%20district%20magistrate%2C%20started%20some%20programmes%20to%20help%20sex%20workers%20in%20the%20area%20learn%20skills%2C%20such%20as%20embroidery%2C%20and%20get%20access%20to%20healthcare.%20Naseema%20took%20part%20in%20one%20such%20programme%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%98Better%20Life%20Option%E2%80%99.%20She%20had%20already%20learnt%20embroidery%20from%20her%20mother%2C%20was%20skilled%20at%20it%2C%20and%20stood%20out.%20But%20even%20then%2C%20she%20struggled%20with%20the%20anxiety%20of%20having%20to%20answer%20certain%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20always%20so%20scared%20that%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20even%20speak.%20Because%20what%20if%20that%20conversation%20leads%20to%20them%20asking%20me%20where%20I%E2%80%99m%20from%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20admits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20just%2013%20years%20old%2C%20she%20was%20forced%20to%20leave%20school%20and%20move%20to%20Sitamarhi%20to%20live%20with%20her%20maternal%20grandmother.%20However%2C%20by%20this%20time%2C%20she%20had%20already%20resolved%20to%20build%20a%20life%20for%20herself%2C%20one%20that%20would%20need%20no%20hiding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CI%20had%20heard%20about%20an%20organisation%20there%20that%20was%20helping%20adolescent%20girls.%20I%20did%20not%20know%20what%20they%20did%20or%20how%20they%20could%20help.%20I%20was%20sure%20that%20if%20I%20just%20tried%20a%20little%2C%20I%20could%20figure%20my%20life%20out%20and%20make%20something%20of%20myself.%20So%2C%20I%20locked%20myself%20in%20a%20room%20for%20days%2C%20refused%20to%20eat%20or%20speak%20to%20anybody%2C%20until%20I%20was%20taken%20to%20where%20that%20organisation%20was%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20father%20kept%20asking%20why%20I%20wanted%20to%20go%20there%2C%20and%20I%20would%20say%20that%20there%20is%20a%20friend%20that%20I%20really%20want%20to%20meet%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20chuckles.%20Her%20persistence%20paid%20off%2C%20and%20one%20day%20she%20met%20with%20the%20people%20from%20%E2%80%98Adithi%E2%80%99%2C%20an%20organisation%20that%20works%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F255139%2Fmumbai-designer-covid19-underprivileged-women-earn-money-donation-livelihood-fashion-cloth-bags-scrunchies-gurmeen-shrivastav-srujna-ngo-india-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderprivileged%20women%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20next%20day%2C%20Adithi%20workers%20came%20to%20her%20house%20and%20urged%20her%20father%20to%20let%20her%20become%20a%20part%20of%20the%20organisation%20where%20she%20would%20learn%20valuable%20skills%20and%20turn%20her%20life%20around.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20so%20stunned%20when%20they%20came%20to%20our%20house.%20It%20was%20like%20my%20legs%20had%20become%20jelly%20and%20the%20cola%20that%20I%20was%20supposed%20to%20serve%20them%2C%20wound%20up%20on%20their%20clothes.%20I%20laugh%20as%20I%20say%20that%20now%2C%20but%20that%20day%20I%20could%20have%20died%20of%20relief%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20worked%20with%20the%20organisation%20till%202002%2C%20becoming%20a%20skilled%20micro-level%20planner%20and%20trainer.%20Her%20years%20in%20Sitamarhi%20with%20Adithi%20taught%20her%20about%20the%20law%2C%20child%20rights%2C%20and%20the%20safety%20the%20Constitution%20grants%20each%20and%20every%20citizen%20of%20this%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Jugnu%E2%80%99%3A%20Where%20children%20express%20their%20dreams%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Naseema%20came%20back%20to%20Muzaffarpur%20in%202002%2C%20she%20saw%20the%20issues%20plaguing%20her%20home%20town%20with%20a%20renewed%20sense%20of%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20a%20raid%20in%20the%20area%20right%20next%20to%20us%2C%20women%20were%20arrested%20and%20taken%20away%20without%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20female%20constable%20because%20those%20rules%2C%20for%20some%20reason%2C%20do%20not%20apply%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20next%20day%2C%20I%20sat%20at%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20tea%20stall%2C%20watching%20as%20the%20police%20rounded%20up%20people%20from%20the%20area.%20A%20meeting%20was%20taking%20place%2C%20led%20by%20the%20%E2%80%98Samaj%20Sudhar%20Committee%E2%80%99%2C%20where%20they%20told%20the%20women%20they%20could%20learn%20skills%20like%20tailoring%2C%20embroidery%2C%20and%20other%20jobs%20offered%20by%20government%20schemes.%20When%20the%20women%20asked%20when%20they%20could%20start%20working%20and%20how%20soon%20they%20would%20get%20the%20money%2C%20they%20were%20told%20it%20would%20take%20six%20months%20to%20set%20up%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20asked%20how%20they%20could%20earn%20a%20living%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20the%20committee%20took%20it%20as%20an%20insult.%20As%20if%20we%20are%20not%20allowed%20to%20ask%20questions%20that%20dictate%20whether%20we%20get%20to%20eat%20two%20meals%20a%20day%20or%20not%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ENaseema%20was%20aware%20of%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20the%20children%20in%20the%20community.%20When%20the%20woman%2C%20often%20the%20primary%20breadwinner%2C%20is%20arrested%2C%20who%20takes%20care%20of%20the%20family%3F%20The%20dependents%2C%20especially%20the%20children%2C%20are%20left%20to%20suffer.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20if%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20young%20girl%20in%20the%20household%2C%20what%20options%20does%20she%20have%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20asks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaseema%E2%80%99s%20work%20with%20Adithi%2C%20along%20with%20her%20increasing%20involvement%20in%20community%20issues%2C%20led%20her%20to%20start%20a%20community-based%20organisation%20called%20%E2%80%98Parcham%E2%80%99%2C%20meaning%20%E